As the mercury continues to rise, it s important to be clear about what exactly such milestones mean, while, at the same time, considering the prospects for mitigating further temperature increases.

First, one year with 1.5 °C or so of warming or one day above 2 °C, as recorded by the European Union s Copernicus program in mid-November (5) doesn t mean we ve already reached those targets as laid out by the Paris Agreement. In order to fulfill Boeing's requirement for a "more-electric" engine, the Trent 1000 is a [[bleedless>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleedless]] design, with power take-off from the intermediate-pressure (IP) spool instead of the high-pressure (HP) spool found in other members of the Trent family. A 2.8 m (110 in) diameter swept-back fan, with a smaller diameter hub to help maximize airflow, was specified. The [[bypass ratio>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bypass_ratio]] has been increased over previous variants by suitable adjustments to the core flow.

A high pressure ratio along with contra-rotating the IP and HP spools improves efficiency.^^[[~[21~]>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rolls-Royce_Trent_1000#cite_note-Green_Engines-21]][//[[failed verification>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability]]//]^^ The use of more legacy components reduces the parts count to minimise maintenance costs. A tiled combustor is featured.

== Operational history ==

On 26 October 2011, the 787 flew its first commercial flight from Tokyo [[Narita Airport>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Narita_Airport]] to [[Hong Kong International Airport>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong_International_Airport]] on All Nippon Airways.^^[[~[22~]>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rolls-Royce_Trent_1000#cite_note-Reuters_Dreamliner_1st_pax-22]]^^ It was powered by Trent 1000 engines.

The 787 was introduced in September 2011 with Package A with 1% worse [[thrust specific fuel consumption>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thrust_specific_fuel_consumption]] (TSFC) than the initial Boeing specification, which was matched by Package B certified in December 2011, then improved by Package C offering 1% better fuel burn than specified and EASA certified in September 2013.^^[[~[23~]>>url:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rolls-Royce_Trent_10"
